cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as MDPs are often used to model concurrent process optimisation problems in multi-agent systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as MDPs are a common tool in AI for decision making under uncertainty.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper mentions scalable learning techniques.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as MDPs are used to model control problems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses a new memory representation for history-dependent schedulers.
